Persidangan ketiga Hubungan Malaysia-Republik Indonesia (2018) anjuran Institut Antarabangsa Polisi Awam dan Pengurusan (INPUMA), Universiti Malaya bertujuan mempertemukan para akademik, pentadbir awam, ahli perniagaan, usahawan, ahli pertubuhan bukan kerajaan (NGO), pengamal media dan para pelajar dari kedua-dua negara (atau negara lain di rantau ini) yang berminat dengan hubungan intra-ASEAN, khususnya Malaysia-Republik Indonesia serta isu dan cabaran semasa yang berkaitan dengannya. eventDescription:
The Center for the Advancement of Language Competence (CALC), Universiti Putra Malaysia (UPM) will be hosting The 1st International Asean English Language teaching Conference 2018 (ASEAN-ELT 2018) from the 15th to 17th March 2018, at the Equatorial Hotel, Melaka. The theme of the conference is “Maximising the Potential in ASEAN Diversities through English”.

This conference is a platform for school teachers and educators to gather and share their best practices through paper and poster presentations. “We are expecting more than 1000 participants to attend this conference and they are mostly school teachers”, says Professor Dr Jayakaran Mukundan, the chairman of the conference. This conference will be jointly organised by several education institution; UIN, Jakarta, NRRU, Thailand, UTHM, UPSI to name a few and several other education institutions. This conference is in support of the teaching of English language which is pertinent in our country and also all over the world. It also acts as a continuous professional development for teachers all over Malaysia and the low conference fee has enable many to attend the conference.

Apart from educators from all over Malaysia, prominent speakers from abroad will also contribute to this conference for example, Professor Alan Maley, a renowned short story writer, a hip hopper Mr Breis, Jan Blake an award winning story teller all from United Kingdom, Professor Carolyn Graham, the founder of jazz chant from the USA, Professor Jack C. Richards from New Zealand to name a few.
This conference is also presenting monetary awards for the “Best English Language Initiatives in School Award” and the “Top English Language Teacher Award”. This has attracted several schools and individual teachers to send in their portfolios to be judged by international judges. These portfolios are very impressive and it will be difficult for the judges to pick the winners.
We hope for this conference to be an eye opener to the teaching and learning with best practices that are shared by many. As of date there are more than 500 abstracts submitted and this will give a variety of choices for teachers to pick as to who they want to listen to. In this time and age teachers need to be exposed to conferences of this nature so that they can be motivated and strive to teach English language in the most interesting and fun way. This will in turn motivate their students to study the language. 
Selected papers from this conference will be compiled and published. For further information please go to www.aseanelt.com or call the number 017 6576598

eventDescription:
Welcome to the International Quantitative Research and Applications Conference 2018 (IQRAC2018)! Universiti Putra Malaysia through the Institute for Mathematical Research (INSPEM) with the Malaysian Academy of Mathematical Scientist (AISMM) are delighted to co-organise IQRAC2018. The conference will be held from 05 -08 August 2018, in the colourful and historic city of Kuching, the capital of the state of Sarawak, Malaysia. We will be working towards a fruitful conference where there is fertile exchange of information on the latest findings in the every changing field of mathematical sciences. As Sarawak pledges to embrace Big Data technology in their efforts for the Sarawak Digital Economy Transformation, it is apt that the IQRAC2018 conference theme reflects the relevance of the mathematical sciences in accepting the challenges of Big Data: “Mathematical Challenges in Big Data Analytics”.

The Organising Committee looks forward to preparing an attractive scientific programme with diverse topics to create a conducive environment suitable for encouraging and facilitating our delegates to share their knowledge and experience. The conference aims to bring together academicians, researchers, practitioners and students of the international mathematical sciences community to discuss various aspects of mathematics with particular emphasis this time on the theme – “Mathematical Challenges in Big Data Analytics”.

The venue of the conference, Kuching, is the perfect setting to highlight the chosen theme of the conference. It is the capital city of Sarawak, the Land of the Hornbills, which houses the seat of state government. Its strategic location on the banks of the Sarawak River has made it the major industrial and commercial centre of East Malaysia. Sarawak is also the largest state of Malaysia with a land mass of almost 125,000 square kilometres. The recent venture to invest in Big Data Analytics in the Digital Economy Transformation efforts reflect Sarawak’s intent to harness the power of Big Data and the research applications related to this to push forward towards economic prosperity.

Sarawak is also home to one of the oldest rainforests in the world, which houses some of the rarest flora and fauna ever discovered. These forests sustains communities of indigenous people that still live in harmony with the land; preserving the practices of their forefathers which allow them to live off the land but not destroy the ecosystem that sustains it. These two facets of Kuching and her ways of balancing both its promising digital economy and her environmental treasure trove is an example of the delicate balance of economic prosperity Sarawak is known for and still being able to preserve and protect the Environment; the two co-existing in perfect harmony.

Kuching means "cat" in Bahasa Malaysia. Like its name, this incredible city has its unique own brand of grace and subtlety as distinct as her people. Interesting fact- the world's first cat museum can be found in Kuching. Despite its status as a capital city and also the centre of the industrial and commercial activities for East Malaysia, Kuching is safe, clean and has a surprising number of tourist attractions. Enjoy finding out her treasures at your own pace.
From rainforest canopies to jungle wildlife, discover the diverse ecosystem of Malaysia's largest state. A state that is chasing modernity yet cloaked with its rich historical charms, Sarawak is a place where commonality and peacefulness is a way of life. A paradise for the adventure buffs, be it from the land to the sea, from mild to vigorous. Whatever the challenge, if you're ready for it, you can be sure Sarawak will give you an experience like no other.

We invite you to discover for yourself our little treasures. We are honoured to host IQRAC2018 here in Kuching, in the great state of Sarawak. We hope you will join us and learn, enjoy, and most importantly be a part of the IQRAC2018 conference. Organise a session, give a talk and remember to experience this great city.
The Organising Committee is looking forward to play host to all members of the mathematical science community at the IQRAC2018 Conference. See you in Kuching Sarawak, MALAYSIA for IQRAC2018!

Putra Green Run 2018 merupakan acara larian yang dianjurkan oleh Universiti Putra Malaysia dengan tujuan untuk meningkatkan kesedaran masyarakat terhadap alam sekitar dan sekali gus memperkasakan amalan kelestarian hijau. Penganjuran larian ini adalah sebahagian daripada kempen kesedaran alam sekitar sejajar dengan Polisi Hijau UPM dan sekali gus mempromosikan persekitaran kampus hijau UPM kepada masyarakat dan meningkatkan keprihatinan masyarakat terhadap kepentingan alam sekitar.

Dengan menyertai Putra Green Run 2018, peserta akan dapat menikmati persekitaran hijau yang kaya dengan tumbuhan, tanaman dan ladang yang sememangnya menjadi daya tarikan di UPM. Kawasan laluan larian ini bukan sahaja menjadi lokasi menarik pelbagai aktiviti penggambaran komersial, malah ia menjadi destinasi pencinta alam sekitar untuk merakamkan keindahan hijau yang mempesonakan.
